---
// src/pages/news/great-spandex-census.astro
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="AARBAA - The Great Spandex Census">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="text-center mt-5 pt-5" 
        style="
          padding-top: 100px !important;
          background-color: #0A3161;
          background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)), url('/images/missioncontrol.jpg');
          background-size: cover !important; 
          background-position: center !important;
          background-repeat: no-repeat !important;
          min-height: 600px;
          color: white;
          margin-top: 76px;
          display: flex;
          align-items: center;
        ">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-lg-10">
                  <div style="background-color: rgba(179, 25, 66, 0.95); display: inline-block; padding: 25px; margin-bottom: 20px; box-shadow: 0 15px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.4); transform: rotate(-1deg);">
                        <h1 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; font-size: 4rem; letter-spacing: 3px; margin: 0; text-transform: uppercase; transform: rotate(1deg);">THE GREAT SPANDEX CENSUS</h1>
                  </div>
                  <p class="lead mb-4">March 22, 2025 | 72 Hours of Surveillance That Changed Everything</p>
                </div>
          </div>
        </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Blog Content Section -->
  <section class="section-padding" style="background-color: #f8f8f8;">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-lg-10">
                  <article class="bg-white p-5 shadow-lg" style="position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
                        <div style="position: absolute; top: -30px; left: -30px; width: 150px; height: 150px; background-color: #B31942; transform: rotate(45deg); z-index: 1;"></div>
                        
                        <div class="problem-text mb-5">
                          <p>OPERATION DOCUMENTATION: PHASE ONE</p>
                          <p>When citizen journalism meets traffic violation accountability.</p>
                        </div>

                        <p class="lead mb-4 text-danger" style="font-weight: bold;">CLASSIFIED: The following report contains data so shocking that cyclist advocacy groups have attempted to suppress its publication.</p>

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #B31942; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #B31942; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">THE NUMBERS THAT SHOCKED A NATION</h2>

                        <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
                          <div class="col-md-3">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0A3161 0%, #1a4b8c 100%); color: white;">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h2 style="font-size: 3rem; margin: 0; color: #FF9933;">1,247</h2>
                                        <p class="mb-0">Red Lights Run</p>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-3">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #B31942 0%, #d62c56 100%); color: white;">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h2 style="font-size: 3rem; margin: 0;">892</h2>
                                        <p class="mb-0">Stop Signs Ignored</p>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-3">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0A3161 0%, #1a4b8c 100%); color: white;">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h2 style="font-size: 3rem; margin: 0; color: #4CAF50;">3,456</h2>
                                        <p class="mb-0">Lane Violations</p>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-3">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm text-center" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #B31942 0%, #d62c56 100%); color: white;">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h2 style="font-size: 3rem; margin: 0;">567</h2>
                                        <p class="mb-0">Near Misses</p>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #B31942; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #B31942; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">THE SURVEILLANCE OPERATION</h2>

                        <p>Armed with nothing but determination, 47 HD cameras, 23 volunteers, and an unhealthy amount of caffeine, AARBAA conducted the most comprehensive cyclist behavior study in American history. Our command center, affectionately dubbed "The War Room," operated 24/7 for 72 consecutive hours across 15 major intersections.</p>

                        <div class="bg-light p-4 my-4" style="border-left: 5px solid #B31942;">
                          <h3 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #B31942;">METHODOLOGY BREAKDOWN</h3>
                          <ul>
                                <li>üé• 47 High-Definition Cameras with Night Vision</li>
                                <li>üìä Custom AI-Powered Violation Detection Software</li>
                                <li>üë• 23 Trained Observers Working in Shifts</li>
                                <li>üìç 15 Strategic Intersection Monitoring Points</li>
                                <li>‚è±Ô∏è 72 Hours of Continuous Surveillance</li>
                                <li>‚òï 847 Cups of Coffee Consumed</li>
                          </ul>
                        </div>

                        <blockquote class="bg-danger text-white p-4 my-4" style="font-style: italic; position: relative;">
                          <div style="position: absolute; top: -15px; left: -15px; width: 50px; height: 50px; background-color: white; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
                          <p>"In 72 hours, we documented more traffic violations than the local police department records in a month. The difference? We were actually looking."</p>
                          <footer class="text-white-50">- Dr. Rebecca Martinez, Lead Data Analyst</footer>
                        </blockquote>

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #0A3161; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #0A3161; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">SHOCKING DISCOVERIES BY TIME OF DAY</h2>

                        <div class="row g-4 mb-4">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                  <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                                        <h4 class="mb-0">Morning Rush (6-9 AM)</h4>
                                  </div>
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <p><strong>Peak Chaos Hours</strong></p>
                                        <ul>
                                          <li>437 red lights run "because I'm late for work"</li>
                                          <li>89% of cyclists rode against traffic at least once</li>
                                          <li>Average speed through stop signs: 18 mph</li>
                                          <li>Coffee cups spotted in water bottle holders: 67</li>
                                        </ul>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                  <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white">
                                        <h4 class="mb-0">Weekend Warriors (Sat-Sun)</h4>
                                  </div>
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <p><strong>Peloton Pandemonium</strong></p>
                                        <ul>
                                          <li>Average group size: 14 cyclists</li>
                                          <li>Maximum simultaneous lane blockage: 4 lanes</li>
                                          <li>Times "STRAVA!" was shouted: 234</li>
                                          <li>Matching outfit coordination score: 94%</li>
                                        </ul>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #B31942; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #B31942; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">THE SPANDEX SPECTRUM ANALYSIS</h2>

                        <div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert" style="border-left: 5px solid #FFC107;">
                          <strong>SCIENTIFIC BREAKTHROUGH:</strong> Our research team discovered a direct correlation between spandex tightness and traffic law violations. The tighter the lycra, the looser the interpretation of road rules.
                        </div>

                        <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
                          <div class="col-12">
                                <div class="card border-0 shadow">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h4 style="color: #B31942;">Violation Rate by Cyclist Category</h4>
                                        <div class="progress mb-3" style="height: 30px;">
                                          <div class="progress-bar bg-danger" role="progressbar" style="width: 95%">Full Lycra Warriors: 95%</div>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="progress mb-3" style="height: 30px;">
                                          <div class="progress-bar bg-warning" role="progressbar" style="width: 78%">Weekend Hobbyists: 78%</div>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="progress mb-3" style="height: 30px;">
                                          <div class="progress-bar bg-info" role="progressbar" style="width: 62%">Commuter Cyclists: 62%</div>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="progress mb-3" style="height: 30px;">
                                          <div class="progress-bar bg-success" role="progressbar" style="width: 41%">Casual Riders: 41%</div>
                                        </div>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #0A3161; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #0A3161; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">MOST CREATIVE EXCUSES DOCUMENTED</h2>

                        <ol class="list-group list-group-numbered mb-5">
                          <li class="list-group-item">"Red lights don't apply when you're maintaining cadence"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"I'm saving the environment, so rules don't apply"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"Cars should thank me for not driving"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"Stop signs are just suggestions for bikes"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"I have right of way because I'm more vulnerable"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"Traffic laws were written before bikes existed"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"My Strava segment time is more important than your schedule"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"I pay taxes too" (Note: Road tax ‚â† Income tax)</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"In Amsterdam, this would be legal"</li>
                          <li class="list-group-item">"My coach said never stop pedaling"</li>
                        </ol>

                        <div class="text-center my-5">
                          <a href="/join" class="btn btn-danger btn-lg px-5 py-3" style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px; box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);">SUPPORT OUR SURVEILLANCE EFFORTS</a>
                        </div>

                        <div class="card bg-light border-0 shadow-sm p-4 my-4">
                          <h3 style="color: #0A3161; border-bottom: 2px solid #0A3161; padding-bottom: 10px;">PHASE TWO: THE ACCOUNTABILITY PROJECT</h3>
                          
                          <p>Following the overwhelming success of The Great Spandex Census, AARBAA is launching Phase Two of our documentation initiative:</p>
                          
                          <div class="row mt-3">
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                              <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                <div class="card-body text-center">
                                  <i class="fas fa-database fa-3x mb-3" style="color: #B31942;"></i>
                                  <h5 class="card-title">National Database</h5>
                                  <p class="card-text">Creating a searchable database of cyclist violations accessible to law enforcement.</p>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                              <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                <div class="card-body text-center">
                                  <i class="fas fa-mobile-alt fa-3x mb-3" style="color: #0A3161;"></i>
                                  <h5 class="card-title">Mobile App</h5>
                                  <p class="card-text">Report cyclist violations in real-time with our upcoming AARBAA Spotter app.</p>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                              <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                <div class="card-body text-center">
                                  <i class="fas fa-trophy fa-3x mb-3" style="color: #FFC107;"></i>
                                  <h5 class="card-title">Reward Program</h5>
                                  <p class="card-text">Earn points for documenting violations. Redeem for AARBAA merchandise!</p>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert" style="border-left: 5px solid #721c24;">
                          <strong>UPDATE:</strong> Local cycling clubs have called our data "misleading" and "taken out of context." We call it "uncomfortably accurate."
                        </div>

                        <hr class="my-5" style="border-top: 2px dashed #B31942;">

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #0A3161; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #0A3161; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">THE HALL OF SHAME</h2>

                        <div class="row">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <img src="/images/bikerpack.png" alt="Pack of Cyclists" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-lg mb-4">
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h4 style="color: #B31942;">Notable Violations Captured</h4>
                            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                              <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üèÜ</span> 
                                <strong>Gold Medal:</strong> Cyclist who ran 17 consecutive red lights while livestreaming
                              </li>
                              <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-secondary me-2">ü•à</span> 
                                <strong>Silver Medal:</strong> Group ride that blocked an ambulance for 3 minutes
                              </li>
                              <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-warning text-dark me-2">ü•â</span> 
                                <strong>Bronze Medal:</strong> Individual who argued with police that "bikes don't need to stop"
                              </li>
                            </ul>
                            
                            <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
                              <strong>Fun Fact:</strong> If each documented violation resulted in the minimum traffic fine, cyclists would owe the city $487,230 in just 72 hours.
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="alert alert-primary mt-5" role="alert" style="border-left: 5px solid #0A3161;">
                          <strong>CALL TO ACTION:</strong> Help us expand The Great Spandex Census to your city! Contact your local AARBAA chapter to organize a surveillance weekend. Together, we can document the truth about cyclist behavior one violation at a time.
                        </div>

                        <p class="text-muted mt-4">Disclaimer: All data collected through legal means in public spaces. No cyclists were directly confronted during surveillance operations, though many were silently judged.</p>

                        <div class="row mt-5">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h3 style="color: #B31942;">Download the Full Report</h3>
                            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                              <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="fas fa-file-pdf me-3 text-danger"></i>
                                <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Complete 147-Page Analysis (PDF)</a>
                              </li>
                              <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="fas fa-file-excel me-3 text-success"></i>
                                <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Raw Data Spreadsheet</a>
                              </li>
                              <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="fas fa-video me-3 text-primary"></i>
                                <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Video Evidence Compilation</a>
                              </li>
                            </ul>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h3 style="color: #B31942;">Share This Investigation</h3>
                            <div class="d-flex gap-2 mt-3">
                              <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-primary"><i class="fab fa-facebook-f"></i></a>
                              <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-info"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a>
                              <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-danger"><i class="fab fa-instagram"></i></a>
                              <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-dark"><i class="fab fa-reddit"></i></a>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                  </article>
                </div>
          </div>
        </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>